The nominations include Sudanâ€™s first female foreign minister, and a former World Bank economist as its new finance minister who will a face an economic crisis that has deepened in recent months. Prime Minister, Abdalla Hamdok, approved them along with 12 other new ministers, a member of the main civilian group in the ruling Sovereign Council said. Asmaa Abdallah had been chosen as Foreign Minister, according to the member of the Forces for Freedom and Change grouping, who spoke on condition of anonymity. Ibrahim Elbadawi would serve as Finance Minister, the source added. Adel Ibrahim was tapped to lead the Energy and Mining Ministry, the source said. General Jamal Aldin Omar will lead the defence portfolio, he added. The government will lead a three-year transition to elections under a power-sharing deal between the military and civilian opposition. Hamdok was expected to announce the full cabinet in the next two days, state news agency SUNA said. --Reuters--